{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"14a490e2-5963-4690-b36b-a53e82527c6f","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. MSTest v3 **dropped support** for several frameworks you're targeting:\n\n1. **`net5.0`** — End-of-life; MSTest v3 requires **net6.0+** for modern .NET.\n2. **`netcoreapp3.1`** — Also EOL and not supported by MSTest v3.\n3. **`net462`** — MSTest v3 raised the minimum .NET Framework to **net462**, so this one *should* still work.\n\n**What you need to do before migrating:**\n\n- Update `net5.0` → `net6.0` (or later, e.g. `net8.0`)\n- Update `netcoreapp3.1` → `net6.0` (or later)\n- `net462` can stay as-is\n\n**Other MSTest v3 breaking changes to watch for:**\n- The separate `MSTest.TestFramework` / `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages are consolidated into a single **`MSTest`** meta-package (recommended but not required).\n- Some deprecated APIs and assertions were removed.\n- `[TestClass]` class-level inheritance behavior changed slightly.\n\nWould you like me to update the `.csproj` to be MSTest v3–ready?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"14a42eb3-7b8c-49f0-8de9-c2fb599e8ba9","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The project multi-targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. MSTest v3 has some important compatibility changes. Let me provide the user with the key issues they'll face.","outputTokens":367,"requestId":"CFCB:B0AF0:6163410:6D772F2:69EC26AD"},"id":"0a8e97ff-d380-4e8d-b03e-103b7129bb48","timestamp":"2026-04-25T02:28:06.275Z","parentId":"88fb7ea8-3296-42d5-b5a2-45c6bcd18b7c"}
